cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with the integration of saliency maps from multiple models, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an arbitrator model that incorporates external knowledge, which suggests that it may fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well. The use of Bayesian integration and deep learning models also indicates that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed model on various datasets suggests that it could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
